description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for one Apprentice Customer Service to work within a reception role to develop their skills within the Operating Theatres Team at Wye Valley NHS Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want our apprentices to provide excellent customer service and administrative support to help with the smooth running of the organisation. As a modern apprentice, you will be supported in providing administrative and clerical support to the Operating Theatres, whilst undertaking an apprenticeship award. You will be required to work as part of a team, communicate effectively and courteously with a wide range of individuals both internally and externally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This Apprenticeship will be a fixed term training contract at 37.5 hours per week, Monday to Friday. You will also have access to the NHS Pension Scheme and will be supported in achieving your NVQ/Diploma L2/3 in Business &amp; Admin.&lt;/p&gt;
